fields.description:
 Hi All,

So AWS JAVA SDK does not work with Eucalyptus from version 1.2.12 onwards. Following are the steps to test this:

{code}
$ git clone https://github.com/amazonwebservices/aws-sdk-for-java.git
$ cd aws-sdk-for-java
$ mv pom.xml /tmp/
$ wget https://raw.github.com/pbailis/aws-java-sdk-dynamodb-timestamp/33d9beb9e8b8bf6965312c2c61c621ce96d054c8/pom.xml
$ change the version in pom.xml to 1.3.14  
$ export MAVEN_OPTS=-Xmx2048M
{code}

We need to replace all the files in aws-sdk-for-java/src/main/java/com/amazonaws/services/storagegateway/model/ and aws-sdk-for-java/src/main/java/com/amazonaws/services/storagegateway/model/transform/ having ISCSI in their names to iSCSI.

{code}
$ mvn install
{code}

The above should give an aws-java-sdk-1.3.14.jar inside aws-sdk-for-java/target/

After that you would need to grab the AWS JAVA SDK from http://sdk-for-java.amazonwebservices.com/latest/aws-java-sdk.zip and unzip it

{code}
$ wget http://sdk-for-java.amazonwebservices.com/latest/aws-java-sdk.zip
$ unzip aws-java-sdk.zip
$ cd aws-java-sdk-1.3.14
$ cd lib/
Copy the aws-java-sdk-1.3.14.jar from earlier maven build to this directory
{code}

Now modify the AwsConsoleApp.java sample program in aws-java-sdk-1.3.14/samples/AwsConsoleApp/

The sample code for AwsConsoleApp.java was modified to only have a EC2 test and endpoint for CLC 3.1 was set

