Did some research and figure that there were 2 modifications in the AWS JAVA SDK that broke this with Eucalyptus.

First commit was when AWS JAVA SDK 1.2.13 came in with some modification in the Signature construction code:

https://github.com/amazonwebservices/aws-sdk-for-java/commit/2b08c776c16fc1c8f5891e93b715ee90a81c287a#L5L13

Noticeably these:

https://github.com/amazonwebservices/aws-sdk-for-java/commit/2b08c776c16fc1c8f5891e93b715ee90a81c287a#L6L93

https://github.com/amazonwebservices/aws-sdk-for-java/commit/2b08c776c16fc1c8f5891e93b715ee90a81c287a#L9L128

Second commit was when they changed 
src/main/java/com/amazonaws/http/HttpRequestFactory.java in the following commit:

https://github.com/amazonwebservices/aws-sdk-for-java/commit/7e8743e346ed20d6cf92d3b20db27082fe596e12

If these changes are reverted in the latest code and it is built the program runs just fine:

